title: Greensboro police officer shot during traffic stop
text:
Greensboro police officer shot during traffic stop 
Posted 5:49 p.m. today Your friends e-mail addresses (comma separated): * Subject: * You must enter the characters with black color that stand out from the other characters More on this 
Greensboro, N.C. â€” A Greensboro police officer was shot Friday around 4:30 p.m. while conducting a traffic stop near Bernau Avenue and Baker Street. 
Another person was shot in the incident, according to a press release. 
Police are on scene interviewing witnesses and gathering more information. 
This is a developing story. Credits
